## Deliverable

`joelclaw briefing --repo <path>` (new CLI command, packages/cli): computes

- **Heading**: active arc / frontier / since-last-session delta — derived
  from the newest observation pages
  (`~/Code/joelhooks/dark-wizard/.brain/observations/*.svx`, schema-v1
  frontmatter) scoped to the repo, plus the day index if present.
- **Memory index**: budgeted (default N=10), repo-scoped entries — title +
  one-line description + page pointer — from observation pages and Brain
  notes relevant to the repo (frontmatter `repos:` when present; path/topic
  heuristics otherwise; recency-ranked v1, interest-decay hooks left as a
  stated TODO for consumption telemetry).
- **Unfold path**: each entry's pointer must resolve in ONE tool call —
  absolute file path (file read first; qmd/Typesense lookup is a later
  layer, do not build it now).
- Sensitive pages (`privacy: sensitive`): include locally-scoped entries but
  mark them `sensitive: true`; never include their body text in the index.
- Output: HATEOAS JSON envelope (house style) AND `--format text` for
  direct prompt injection.

DO NOT build the injectors (claude hook / pi extension / codex wiring) —
that is a separate blocked question. Your receipt is the computation:
running `joelclaw briefing --repo ~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-observer` and
`--repo ~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-wiki` yields DIFFERENT, correctly-scoped
indexes with real page pointers that resolve.

